{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Adapters in multimodal models can play a unique role that serves as a bridge to convert the features in a modality to another modality, thus integrating the multimodal data with low costs.",
    "Several approaches [258], [260]- [263], [267] utilized simple projection layers to convert medical visual features into text embeddings, likely serving as a visual-based soft prompt for the text encoder.",
    "Specially, M 3 AD [264] incorporated general adapters into two unimodal encoding networks and also employed a modalityfusion adapter to enhance multimodal interactions.",
    "In general, the adapters in MFMs convert different modalities being lightweight and economical to facilitate seamless integration.",
    "c) PE-based adaptation methods in MFMs is also flourishing."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
